    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_9724148" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/9724148" />
    <a title="Russell" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/607453-russell"><img alt="Russell" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1196798503p2/607453.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/9724148?book_show_action=true">Nov 29, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Russell" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Russell" href="/user/show/607453-russell">Russell</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer9724148" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3207902347066570552">Several years before the X-files movie, Sidney Sheldon (writer of &quot;I Dream of Jeannie&quot;) wrote this thriller about aliens and government cover ups.<br/><br/>It&apos;s pretty silly over all. What was weird, though, is that Sheldon includes a bunch of real evidence of a government conspiracy in the book&apos;s postscript (dozens of scientists who worked on Reagan&apos;s Star Wars who mysteriously died).<br/><br/>Moral of the story: Don&apos;t read books off of your mom&apos;s bookshelf even if you&apos;re really bored. </span>
  <span id="freeText3207902347066570552" style="display:none">Several years before the X-files movie, Sidney Sheldon (writer of "I Dream of Jeannie") wrote this thriller about aliens and government cover ups.<br /><br />It's pretty silly over all. What was weird, though, is that Sheldon includes a bunch of real evidence of a government conspiracy in the book's postscript (dozens of scientists who worked on Reagan's Star Wars who mysteriously died).<br /><br />Moral of the story: Don't read books off of your mom's bookshelf even if you're really bored. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3207902347066570552" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
