<div id="review_600979287" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/600979287" />
    <a title="Sana&#39;a Abdul latheef" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14283260-sana-a-abdul-latheef"><img alt="Sana&#39;a Abdul latheef" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1352122446p2/14283260.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/600979287?book_show_action=true">Apr 27, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sana&#39;a Abdul latheef" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sana&#39;a Abdul latheef" href="/user/show/14283260-sana-a-abdul-latheef">Sana&#39;a Abdul latheef</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">no one</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer600979287&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer600979287" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2485586982581120337">When I was reading the critical parts of this book, I was like, &quot;Oh please no....don&apos;t suggest that.....no...no....don&apos;t end it with aliens&quot;...and then he did exactly that! Why does it always end up with aliens? Aliens are so...very, very boring. I think bringing up aliens in any story is like a last resort of writers, like &apos;when in doubt, put aliens there&apos;. I bought this book without realizing it was sci-fi. That was foolish on my part. The reason I bought this was because of the author&apos;s fame </span>
  <span id="freeText2485586982581120337" style="display:none">When I was reading the critical parts of this book, I was like, "Oh please no....don't suggest that.....no...no....don't end it with aliens"...and then he did exactly that! Why does it always end up with aliens? Aliens are so...very, very boring. I think bringing up aliens in any story is like a last resort of writers, like 'when in doubt, put aliens there'. I bought this book without realizing it was sci-fi. That was foolish on my part. The reason I bought this was because of the author's fame in the international level. I might read his books again, if he has written any non sci-fi that is, but I certainly wont be buying any without assurance. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2485586982581120337" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


